Your social security number

Line 1. If filing Schedule A (Form 1040), enter the amount from Form 1040, line 41, and go to line 2. Otherwise enter the amount from Form 1040, line 38, and go to line 7. (If less than zero, enter as a negative amount).
Line 2. Medical and dental. If you or your spouse was 65 or older, enter the smaller of Schedule A (Form 1040), line 4, or 2.5% (.025) of Form 1040, line 38. If zero or less, enter zero.
Line 4. Enter the home mortgage interest adjustment, if any, from line 6 of the worksheet in the instructions for this line.
Line 6. If Form 1040, line 38, is $150,000 or less, enter zero. Otherwise, see instructions.
Line 7. Tax refund from Form 1040, line 10 or line 21.
Line 8. Investment interest expense (difference between regular tax and AMT).
Line 9. Depletion (difference between regular tax and AMT).
Line 10. Net operating loss deduction from Form 1040, line 21. Enter as a positive amount.
Line 11. Alternative tax net operating loss deduction.
Line 12. Interest from specified private activity bonds exempt from the regular tax.
Line 13. Qualified small business stock (7% of gain excluded under Section 1202).
Line 14. Exercise of incentive stock options (excess of AMT income over regular tax income).
Line 15. Estates and trusts (amount from Schedule K-1) (Form 1041), box 12, code A.
Line 16. Electing large partnerships (amount from Schedule K-1 (Form 1065-B), box 6).
Line 17. Disposition of property (difference between AMT and regular tax gain or loss).
Line 18. Depreciation on assets placed in service after 1986 (difference between regular tax and AMT).
Line 19. Passive activities (difference between AMT and regular tax income or loss).
Line 20. Loss limitations (difference between AMT and regular tax income or loss).
Line 21. Circulation costs (difference between regular tax and AMT).
Line 22. Long-term contracts (difference between AMT and regular tax income).
Line 23. Mining costs (difference between regular tax and AMT).
Line 24. Research and experimental costs (difference between regular tax and AMT).
Line 25. Income from certain installment sales before January 1, 1987.
Line 26. Intangible drilling costs preference.
Line 27. Other adjustments, including income-based related adjustments.
Line 28. Alternative minimum taxable income. Combine lines 1 through 27. (If married filing separately and line 28 is more $238,550, see instructions).
Line 29. Exemption.

Line 31. If you are filing Form 2555 or 2555-EZ, see instructions for the amount to enter. If you reported capital gain distributions directly on Form 1040, line 13; you reported qualified dividends on Form 1040, line 9b; or you had a gain on both lines 15 and 16 of Schedule D (Form 1040) (as refigured for the AMT, if necessary), complete Part III on the back and enter the amount from line 60 here. All others: If line 30 is $179,500 or less ($89,750 or less if married filing separately). multiply line 30 by 26% (.26). Otherwise, multiply line 30 by 28% (.28) and subtract $3,590 ($1,795 if married filing separately) from the result.
Line 32. Alternative minimum tax foreign tax credit (see instructions).

Line 34. Tax from Form 1040, line 44 (minus any tax from Form 4972 and any foreign tax credit from Form 1040, line 47). If you used Schedule J to figure your tax , the amount from line 44 of Form 1040 must be refigured without using Schedule J.
